Rating: 0
IT would be nice if the author of this recipe had named the ingredients for herbs de provence. Ingredients: 1 tablespoon thyme, 1 tablespoon chervil, 1 tablespoon rosemary, 1 tablespoon summer savory, 1 teaspoon lavender, 1 teaspoon tarragon, 1 teaspoon marjoram, 1/2 teaspoon oregano, 1/2 teaspoon mint, 2 powdered or chopped bay leaves. A simpler bouquet can be made with a mixture of savory, rosemary, fennel, basil, thyme, and lavender. Lavender is an essential ingredient of herbes de provence, while thyme usually dominates the taste of the herb mixture.

